OL,3,CBoy 'hallucinated and clawed his face'
OL,4,Cafter drinking slushy, mother says
OL,6,FAlbie Pegg, four, was rushed through
OL,7,FA&E after becoming lethargic, within
OL,8,Fhours he was "completely
OL,9,Funresponsive," his mother told ITV
OL,10,FNews.
OL,12,FHis mother, Beth Green said: "He had
OL,13,Fstarted hallucinating, he had started
OL,14,Fclawing at himself, biting me, biting
OL,15,Fhimself, we could not comprehend what
OL,16,Fhad happened to him.
OL,18,F"By the time we got to A&E he was a
OL,19,Fdead weight, I had to fire lift him
OL,20,Fin, just completely unresponsive."
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G2/8
