OL,3,CBoy 'hallucinated and clawed his face'
OL,4,Cafter drinking slushy, mother says
OL,6,F"We were completely shocked ... he's
OL,7,Fthis little energetic ball of fun
OL,8,Freally, to see him go that drastically
OL,9,Fbad in such a short space of time,
OL,10,Fit's heart breaking."
OL,12,FAlbie, who lives in Nuneaton, was in
OL,13,Fhospital for four days last year, with
OL,14,Fdoctors "still stumped" as to what had
OL,15,Fcaused his reaction when he was
OL,16,Fdischarged, his mother said.
OL,18,FMonths later his test results showed
OL,19,Fthe additive glycerol in the slushy,
OL,20,Fwhich gives the drink its texture, had
OL,21,Fcaused Albie's illness.
OL,1,Wz5~k4~k7}hw1 ~k4~sj5j5~s1 G     G3/8
